The paper deals with the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The paper also mentions the algebraic dichotomy conjecture, which is a well-known open problem in the field. Based on this, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses list homomorphism problems and graphs, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry), respectively. The paper's focus on computational problems and algorithms suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
